{
  "body": "Create a hyper-realistic editorial film portrait, single subject, single frame, like a real photograph pulled out of a magazine — not concept art, not 3D render, not AI-glossy.\n\nSubject\n{{subject}}\n\nScene & atmosphere\n- Setting: {{scene}}\n- Mood: {{mood}}\n- Pose & gaze: {{pose_and_gaze}}\n- The image must feel observed, not directed. Imperfect composition, real body weight, real fabric drape.\n\nCamera & film\n- Film / camera signature: {{film_stock}}\n- Lens & aperture: {{lens_and_aperture}}\n- Lighting: {{lighting}}\n- Use specifications, not adjectives — `f/1.8`, `50mm`, `1/125s`, `ISO 400` beat \"shallow depth of field\".\n- Authentic film characteristics: subtle grain, gentle color shift, soft highlight bloom, natural lens vignetting, true-to-stock color science. No digital over-sharpening, no clarity slider abuse.\n\nSkin & realism\n- Visible skin texture: micro pores, fine peach fuzz, a hint of unevenness in tone. A few subtle freckles or moles where natural.\n- No plastic skin, no porcelain smoothing, no liquify, no airbrushing, no blemish removal.\n- Hair has individual stray strands and natural volume — not a 3D wig.\n- Fabric has real wrinkles and weight.\n\nComposition\n- Slightly off-center subject, generous negative space, intentional crop. Allow a part of the body or hair to bleed off-frame.\n- The image should look like one frame from a roll of film — not a perfect studio capture.\n\nStrict avoid\n- No watermark, no text overlay, no caption.\n- No glossy retouched skin, no symmetrical Instagram-filter look, no over-saturated color.\n- No extra limbs, no warped hands, no melted earrings, no broken anatomy.\n- No fake bokeh balls, no plastic catchlight stars, no AI-style \"painted\" eyes.\n\nOutput aspect ratio: {{aspect_ratio}}.\n\n——————\nSubject: {{subject}}\nScene: {{scene}}\nFilm: {{film_stock}}\nLens: {{lens_and_aperture}}\nLighting: {{lighting}}\nPose: {{pose_and_gaze}}\nMood: {{mood}}\nAspect: {{aspect_ratio}}\n",
